data.summary_suggestion: Cancel an active extractor crawl run
data.description_suggestion: Cancels an active crawl run for the specified extractor. Requires the extractorId of the crawl to be terminated. The operation will stop the extractor from processing further data and return the updated crawl run status. Only active crawl runs can be cancelled; attempting to cancel a completed or already-cancelled run will return an error.

data.current_summary: Launch a crawl from an extractor that a user owns.
data.summary_suggestion: Start a new crawl run for an extractor
data.description_suggestion: Initiates a new crawl run using the specified extractor. Requires the extractorId of an extractor owned by the authenticated user. The operation queues the crawl for execution and returns a CrawlRun object containing the run ID and initial status. The crawl will begin processing asynchronously. Returns 200 with the created crawl run details on success.
